cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM

This paper is about improving the performance of convolutional neural networks for image classification and recognition tasks. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses various optimization techniques and activation functions, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper proposes a new framework for concatenating multi-scale features, which could fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) or cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper evaluates its approach on various benchmark datasets, which could also place it under cs.MM (Multimedia).
